CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 28, 1971, pg. 29 reads: "Boycott - Scenes as members of the United Farm Workers, Al-CIO started picketing a Pittsburgh outlet of Kentucky Fried Chicken in connection with a nationwide boycott against the firm in 40 states. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men walking on sidewalk holding signs protesting against Port Authority, Kentucky Fried Chicken, Smirnoff, and Italian Swiss Colony Wines, with billboard for Parliament cigarettes in background
